Package com.gemalto.idp.mobile.msp

Interface MspField

public interface MspField
A class represents the MSP field which describes the field information such as field completeness. This class also is a helper class to work with UI components for the partial input from end users.
Since:
4.5

  • Method Details

    • getMissingBytes

      Map<Integer,Byte> getMissingBytes()
      Get the missing bytes of current MspField. Also, see isComplete() to check if the current MspFiled is incomplete. The returned value is a map with key being the index of the missing byte and the value being '0x7F'. This API is to facilitate developers with UI handling, e.g. they may need to display something like "123x5x7x9x", the returned value for this case will be as below: {{3, 0x7f}, {5, 0x7F}, {7, 0x7F}, {9, 0x7F}}
      Returns:
      a map of all the missing bytes.
      Since:
      4.5
      See Also:
      • getVisibleBytes()
      • updateMissingBytes(Map)

    • getVisibleBytes

      Map<Integer,Byte> getVisibleBytes()
      Get the visible bytes of current MspField. Also, see isComplete() to check if the current MspFiled is incomplete. The returned value is a map with key being the index of the visible byte and the value. This API is to facilitate developers with UI handling, e.g. they may need to display something like "123x5x7x9x", the returned value for this case will be as below: {{0, 1}, {1, 2}, {2, 3}, {4, 5}, {6, 7}, {8, 9}}
      Returns:
      a map of all the visible bytes.
      Since:
      4.5
      See Also:
      • getMissingBytes()
      • updateMissingBytes(Map)

      int updateMissingBytes(Map<Integer,Byte> missingBytes)

      Returns:
